  "text": "Both the trapezoidal Newton's method and the midpoint Newton's method are of cubic order, while the original Newton's method was of quadratic order. A variety of methods can be applied to the x * in addition to Newton's method. Petković [CITATION_1] derived the following simultaneous method for finding all simple zeros of polynomials by applying the Weierstrass method to the x * in the midpoint Newton's method:",
